<paragraph base="SL33603" principles="yes" id="IAS41_10"><paranum>10</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 41"/><data name="paranum" value="10"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS41_P0157">An entity shall recognise a <xref base="SL143220" href="IAS41_5.dita#IAS41_5/IAS41_P0108">biological asset<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0021"/></ph></xref> or <xref base="SL143219" href="IAS41_5.dita#IAS41_5/IAS41_P0107">agricultural produce<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0011"/></ph></xref> when, and only when: </p><ol base="SL143249" type="lower-alpha" id="IAS41_L0010"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value>         <p base="SL143251" id="IAS41_P0158">the entity controls                      the asset as a result of past events;</p>       </li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value>         <p base="SL143253" id="IAS41_P0159">it is probable that future economic benefits                      associated with the asset will flow to the entity; and</p>       </li><li><li_value>(c)</li_value>         <p base="SL143255" id="IAS41_P0160">the <xref base="SL143246" href="IAS41_8.dita#IAS41_8/IAS41_P0150">fair value<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0118"/></ph></xref> or cost of the asset can be measured reliably.</p>       </li></ol></body></paragraph>